<dashboard script="entropy_lab.js" version="1.1" hideEdit="true">
  <label>Entropy lab</label>
  <description>Explore entropy scores: maximum possible values, single strings, and batch scoring against every model in the app.</description>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>1. Maximum possible entropy</title>
      <html>
        <style>
          .lab-note { background: #f4f6f8; border-left: 3px solid #5c6bc0; padding: 8px 12px; margin: 8px 0 14px; }
          .lab-field { margin: 10px 0; }
          .lab-field label { font-weight: 600; margin-right: 8px; }
          .lab-field input[type="text"], .lab-field input[type="number"] { padding: 4px 8px; width: 140px; }
          .lab-scroll { max-height: 420px; overflow-y: auto; border: 1px solid #d5dbe0; display: inline-block; min-width: 320px; }
          .lab-table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }
          .lab-table th, .lab-table td { border-bottom: 1px solid #e3e7ea; padding: 3px 12px; text-align: left; font-family: monospace; }
          .lab-table th { position: sticky; top: 0; background: #eceff1; font-family: inherit; }
          .lab-err { color: #b0321c; font-weight: 600; }
          .lab-stats { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin: 10px 0; }
          .lab-stat-card { border: 1px solid #d5dbe0; border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 14px; background: #fafbfc; }
          .lab-stat-card .k { font-size: 11px; color: #6b7785; text-transform: uppercase; }
          .lab-stat-card .v { font-family: monospace; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; }
          .lab-model-block h4 { margin: 14px 0 4px; }
          textarea#lab-single-input { width: 100%; max-width: 640px; height: 56px; font-family: monospace; }
          .lab-muted { color: #6b7785; font-size: 12px; }
          #lab-max-value { font-family: monospace; font-size: 34px; font-weight: 700; margin: 6px 0 2px; }
          #lab-max-formula { font-family: monospace; color: #6b7785; }
        </style>
        <div class="lab-note">
          The maximum score a string can get is <b>-log2(floor)</b> bits per
          bigram: a string whose every bigram is unknown to the model (e.g. a
          run of digits &#8212; bigram tables contain no digits, so the choice of
          probability model is irrelevant) scores the floor probability on
          every bigram. Because the score is normalized per bigram, this
          maximum is the same for every string length &#8805; 2; strings shorter
          than 2 characters contain no bigrams and get no score at all.
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <label for="lab-max-floor">Floor:</label>
          <input type="text" id="lab-max-floor" value="1e-7"/>
          <button id="lab-max-btn" class="btn btn-primary">Compute</button>
        </div>
        <div id="lab-max-value">&#8212;</div>
        <div id="lab-max-formula"></div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>2. Score a single string</title>
      <html>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <textarea id="lab-single-input" placeholder="e.g. niestowarzyszona or a3f9bb12.cdn77.net"></textarea>
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <label for="lab-single-model">Model:</label>
          <select id="lab-single-model">
            <option value="*">* (all models)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <button id="lab-single-btn" class="btn btn-primary">Score</button>
          <span class="lab-muted">spaces, dots, commas, hyphens and underscores are stripped; input is lowercased</span>
        </div>
        <div id="lab-single-out"></div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>3. Batch scoring from a file</title>
      <html>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <label for="lab-batch-file">File with strings (one per line):</label>
          <input type="file" id="lab-batch-file" accept=".txt,.csv,text/plain,text/csv"/>
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <label for="lab-batch-model">Model:</label>
          <select id="lab-batch-model">
            <option value="*">* (all models)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <label for="lab-batch-floor">Floor:</label>
          <input type="text" id="lab-batch-floor" placeholder="default: 1e-7"/>
          <span class="lab-muted">probability for bigrams unknown to the model; leave empty to use the default</span>
        </div>
        <div class="lab-field">
          <button id="lab-batch-btn" class="btn btn-primary">Score file</button>
          <button id="lab-batch-csv" class="btn" style="display:none;">Download results as CSV</button>
          <span class="lab-muted">up to 200 000 lines; pick a model or * to score against every model in the lookups folder</span>
        </div>
        <div id="lab-batch-stats"></div>
        <div id="lab-batch-info" class="lab-muted"></div>
        <div class="lab-scroll" style="max-height: 420px; min-width: 60%;">
          <table class="lab-table" id="lab-batch-table">
            <thead></thead>
            <tbody></tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
</dashboard>
